===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|semen|t=to seem, befit, be becoming}}, from {{der|en|non|sœma|t=to conform to, beseem, befit}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*sōmijaną|t=to unite, fit}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*sem-|t=one; whole}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|seme|t=to be fitting; beseem}}, {{cog|da|sømme|t=to beseem}},  {{cog|gmq-osw|søma}}, {{cog|fo|søma|t=to be proper}}. Related also to {{cog|non|sómi|t=honour}} ( > archaic {{cog|da|somme|t=decent comportment}}), {{cog|non|sœmr|t=fitting, seemly}}, {{cog|ang|sēman|t=to reconcile, bring an agreement}}, {{cog|ang|sōm||agreement}}.

